---
import ArticleLayout from "../../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "A 5-Minute Checklist Before Your Cleaning Visit | Expert Tips | Empire Cleaning Group";
const heading = "A 5-Minute Checklist Before Your Cleaning Visit";
const description =
  "Simple preparation steps to help your appointment run smoothly and efficiently.";
---

<ArticleLayout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={description}
  heading={heading}
  backHref="/en/conseils"
  backLabel="← Back to expert tips"
>
  <div class="article-meta" style="margin-bottom: 2rem; color: #666; font-style: italic;">
    <span>Category: Guide</span> | <span>Updated: December 12, 2024</span>
  </div>

  <p class="lead" style="font-size: 1.2rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--color-primary); font-weight: 500;">
    A little preparation helps your technician work faster and deliver the best result.
  </p>

  <div
    style="background-color: #f8f9fa; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent); padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; border-radius: 4px;"
  >
    <p style="margin: 0;">
      <strong>Tip:</strong> clearing fragile items and tight areas first lets us focus on deep cleaning—not moving
      décor.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>1) Clear work areas</h2>
  <p>Move fragile items, toys, and small objects from the areas to be cleaned.</p>

  <h2>2) Furniture expectations</h2>
  <p>
    Most standard furniture can be moved, but heavy or sensitive items should stay in place for safety.
  </p>

  <h2>3) Light vacuuming (optional)</h2>
  <p>A quick vacuum pass can help remove surface debris before deep extraction.</p>

  <h2>4) Parking access</h2>
  <p>Closer truck access supports stronger heat and consistent equipment performance.</p>
</ArticleLayout>
